| Spotify: Now Play  | `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.spotify-now-playing`| none              | Show track + play/pause control       |
| Spotify: Previous  | `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.spotify-previous`   | none              | Previous track                        |
| Spotify: Next      | `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.spotify-next`       | none              | Next track                            |
| Spotify: Like      | `dev.aryapaw.quickbits.spotify-like`       | none              | Toggle liked status                   |

## Spotify Integration

**Architecture:**
- `SpotifyAuth`: OAuth 2.0 flow with local HTTP server (port 5789)
- `SpotifyAPI`: Web API wrapper (getCurrentTrack, playPause, etc.)
- `SpotifyState`: Centralized polling (500ms) with event subscriptions
- Global settings storage via Stream Deck SDK

**OAuth Flow:**
1. User opens Setup page ‚Üí enters Client ID/Secret
2. Redirect to Spotify authorization
3. Callback exchanges code for access + refresh tokens
4. Tokens stored in Stream Deck global settings

**State Management:**
- Single polling loop (500ms interval) when actions visible
- All actions subscribe to state changes
- Automatic token refresh on 401

**Scopes:**
- `user-read-playback-state`
- `user-modify-playback-state`
- `user-read-currently-playing`
- `user-library-read`
- `user-library-modify`

## Process Management

**ProcessManager** (`src/shared/process-manager.ts`):
- `spawn` with `detached: true` for short-lived trigger exes (Windows)
- `startGuiTriggerProcess`: `windowsHide: false` so WinForms can foreground

**SkydimoLightingToggleAction** (`skydimo-lighting-toggle.ts`):
- Launches `SkydimoTrigger.ScreenSync.exe` or `SkydimoTrigger.ScreenStatic.exe` (WinForms, brief foreground, auto-exit)
- Key UI: **single** manifest state; `setImage(static|sync)` + `setTitle` (avoids `setState` / dual-state title quirks)
- Persists last mode in action settings (`screenSyncActive`); not a live Skydimo API read

## Helper Commands

```bash
QuickbitsHelper.exe set-volume --percent <0-100>
QuickbitsHelper.exe toggle-dnd
```

## Windows APIs Used

- **Volume**: Core Audio API (IMMDeviceEnumerator, IAudioEndpointVolume)
- **Keyboard simulation**: `keybd_event` for reliable background input
- **DND**: UI macro (Win+N, Enter, Esc)

## Important Notes

- Helper must be self-contained (`SelfContained=true`) to avoid DLL dependencies
- Use `keybd_event` instead of `SendInput` for background processes
- Volume flyout: press VolumeDown then VolumeUp to trigger system UI
